Okay my bad.
But you can admit it is not easy to find stuff when everything is in the same thread.

Nothing forces you to be pedantic too :-)

You can also recompress the files with tools like XnConvert, you will strip any metadata and reduce the file size by 40% with the same quality, making the file impossible to track and easier to share.

I always recrompress in JPEG at 95% quality, it lets my harddrive breath (Pride1.jpg is 3MB instead of 7MB for instance) and the difference is invisible to any normal human being :)

>>bd94d546-6126-4edd-b516-06927ef8ac33
Yes I had the problem, open the Zero menu and click "Rebuild" under "Database".

>>d0623af6-4bcf-4998-a1df-b795ff810f66
Unfortunately it is not that simple. Because it can be fixed locally does not mean it is a local problem.
Being myself a software developper, more than once I made a mistake on the server which required users to clean their cookies to "repair" the problem, and dependeing on the problem it might or might not affect everyone.
It is more likely that millchan devs changed something that somehow corrupted the database for a few users (I too had to rebuild the database).

No need to be condescending to users which don't have the knowledge to fix it themself.
